pull.title: Slightly overhaul NSI pixmaps
pull.body:
Slightly overhaul the NSI pixmaps.
As far as I can see the `share/pixmaps/bitcoin*.png|.xmp` files are unused (removed in this PR).

Gitian build will follow.

events.body: Gitian build: https://bitcoin.jonasschnelli.ch/build/188 How it looks after this PR:

Looks like they are used in contrib.

utACK on the other change.

```sh
git grep xpm ./contrib/
contrib/debian/bitcoin-qt.install:share/pixmaps/bitcoin32.xpm usr/share/pixmaps
contrib/debian/bitcoin-qt.install:share/pixmaps/bitcoin16.xpm usr/share/pixmaps
contrib/rpm/bitcoin.spec:%{_bindir}/convert -resize 16x16 %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin256.png %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin16.xpm
contrib/rpm/bitcoin.spec:%{_bindir}/convert -resize 32x32 %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin256.png %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin32.xpm
contrib/rpm/bitcoin.spec:%{_bindir}/convert -resize 64x64 %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin256.png %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin64.xpm
contrib/rpm/bitcoin.spec:%{_bindir}/convert -resize 128x128 %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin256.png %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin128.xpm
contrib/rpm/bitcoin.spec:%{_bindir}/convert %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin256.png %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/bitcoin256.xpm
contrib/rpm/bitcoin.spec:touch %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/pixmaps/*.xpm -r %{SOURCE100}
contrib/rpm/bitcoin.spec:%attr(0644,root,root) %{_datadir}/pixmaps/*.xpm
